claims:
Claims Claims Device for image recording, the device comprising: a guiding device (1) configured to guide at least an object (2) in an object plane (la); at least a driving device (3) configured to transport the object (2) in the object plane (la) in a transport direction (4); an image plane (5); at least a contact image sensor comprising at least a light source (6) for illuminating of the object (2), at least a light-sensitive line-pixel array (7), wherein the light-sensitive line-pixel array (7) is arranged in a direction transverse to the transport direction (4) and is arranged in the image plane (5), a control device (8) configured to control the light source (6) and/or the light-sensitive line-pixel array (7) and configured to determine a signal generated by the light-sensitive line-pixel array (7), and an optical device (9) arranged between the object plane (la) and the image plane (5), wherein the optical device (9) comprises at least a plurality of rod lenses (10), wherein the rod lenses (10) are arranged in at least one row (14a, 14b) in the direction transverse to the transport direction (4) of the object (2), and wherein the optical device (9) is configured to guide a light beam (13) emitted from the light source (6) and partially reflected by the object (2) via at least the rod lenses (10) to the light-sensitive line-pixel array (7) and configured to broaden a sampled area in the transport direction (4) before the light beam incides at the light-sensitive line-pixel array (7); wherein the optical device (9) comprises one or more inlet surfaces being inclined by a predetermined angle (a) with regard to a plane (P), wherein the plane (P) is orthogonal to a longitudinal axis (L) of each rod lens (10a, 10b) of the plurality of rod lenses (10); 

wherein the one or more inlet surfaces are provided by at least one correction prism (12) or are provided by the plurality of rod lenses (10). The device according to claim 1, wherein the one or more inlet surfaces are configured to refract the light beam such that a first portion of the light beam and a second portion of the light beam intersect before or at inciding at the object plane (la); and/or wherein the one or more inlet surfaces face the object plane (la). The device according to claim 1 or 2, wherein the optical device (9) is configured to guide the light beam and to overlap at least a first portion of the light beam and a second portion of the light beam, and/or wherein the optical device (9) is configured to reduce a scanning step (14) in the object plane (la) by a value of 1/4. The device according to anyone of the foregoing claims, wherein the optical device (9) comprises at least a correction lens (11) configured to broaden the light beam and a sampling area in the transport direction (4) on the object plane (la), and/or wherein the correction lens (11) is a cylindrical diverging lens and/or a piano concave cylindrical lens. The device according to anyone of the foregoing claims, wherein the correction lens (11) is configured to cover the at least one row of the rod lenses (10) and/or the lightsensitive line-pixel array (7) in the direction transverse to the transport direction (4). The device according to anyone of the foregoing claims, wherein the correction prism (12) and/or the correction lens (11) are arranged between the rod lenses (10) and the line-pixel array (7) and/or the image plane (5). 7. The device according to anyone of claims 1 to 6, wherein the optical device (9) comprises the at least a correction prism (12) configured to split the light beam in the transport direction (4) and to broaden a sampling area in the transport direction (4) of the object (2) on the object plane (la). 8. The device according to one of claims 1 to 7, wherein the correction prism (12) is a triangular prism and/or the one or more inlet surfaces provided by the correction prism (12) are inclined in relation to an outlet surface (12b) of a base area of the correction prism (12) by the predetermined angle (a). 9. The device according to one of claims 1 or 8, wherein the rod lenses (10) are arranged in two rows, wherein the two rows are arranged adjacently and parallelly, wherein, preferably, a first row of the two rows is displaced from a second row of the two rows in the direction transverse to the transport direction (4) by a predetermined distance, and/or wherein, preferably, an area between the two rows is filled by an adhesive fill material. 10. The device according to claim 9, wherein the correction prism (12) is configured to be arranged adjacent to the two rows of rod lenses (10) and configured to cover at least two adjacent rod lenses (10a, 10b) of different rows of the two rows in the transport direction (4), respectively. 11. The device according to anyone claim 9 or 10, wherein at least one first rod lens of a first row of the two rows (10a, 10b) includes a first inlet surface of the one or more inlet surfaces; wherein at least one second rod lens of a second row of the two rows (10a, 10b) is arranged adjacent to the at least one first rod lens and includes a second inlet surface of the one or more inlet surfaces; 

 wherein the first inlet surface and the second inlet surface are inclined with regard to each other, preferably by twice the predetermined angle (a). 12. The device according to anyone of claims 9 to 11, wherein each rod lens (10a, 10b) of the two rows includes an inlet surface of the one or more inlet surfaces, which is inclined by the predetermined angle (a) with regard to the plane (P), which is orthogonal to the longitudinal axis (L) of each rod lens (10a, 10b). 13. The device according to anyone of claims 9 to 12, wherein a height of a first lateral surface (lOe) of the rod lens (10a) of the first row and a height of a first lateral surface (1 Of) of the rod lens (10b) of the second row are equal, wherein a height of a second lateral surface (10g) of the rod lens (10a) of the first row and a height of a second lateral surface (lOh) of the rod lens (10b) of the second row are equal, wherein the two first lateral surfaces (lOe, 1 Of) are arranged closer to each other than the two second lateral surfaces (10g, lOh), and wherein the heights of the two first lateral surfaces (lOe, I Of) are greater than the heights of the two second lateral surfaces (10g, lOh), or wherein the heights of the two second lateral surfaces (10g, lOh) are greater than the heights of the two first lateral surfaces (lOe, 1 Of). 14. The device according to anyone of claims 1 to 13, wherein at least one of the one or more inlet surfaces is orientated towards the object plane (la) and/or wherein at least one of the one or more inlet surfaces is curved. 15. The device according to any of claims 1 to 12, wherein the predetermined angle (a) is a value of 2.6 degrees. 

A method for image recording, the method comprising: Guiding at least an object (2) in an object plane (la) using a guiding device (1), Transporting the object (2) in the object plane (la) in a transport direction (4) using at least a driving device (3), Illuminating the object (2) using at least a light source (8) of at least a contact image sensor, Controlling the light source (8) and/or a light-sensitive line-pixel array (7) of the contact image sensor using the control device (6), Determining a signal generated by the light-sensitive line-pixel array (7) in an image plane (5) using the control device (6), Guiding a light beam emitted from the light source (8) and partially reflected by the object (2) via at least rod lenses (10) to a light-sensitive line-pixel array (7) using an optical device (9), wherein the optical device (9) comprises at least the rod lenses (10), and Broadening by the optical device (9) the light beam in the transport direction (4) of the object (2) before the light beam incides at the light-sensitive line-pixel array (7); wherein the optical device (9) comprises one or more inlet surfaces being inclined by a predetermined angle (a) with regard to a plane (P), which is orthogonal to a longitudinal axis (L) of each of the rod lenses (10); wherein the one or more inlet surfaces are provided by at least one correction prism (12) or are provided by the rod lenses (10).
